  "texts": [
    "Each instance is characterized by an initial condition u 0 ∈ L 2 (Ω, R du) and a set of parameters γ = (b, f, c), which include boundary conditions b ∈ L 2 (∂Ω × [0, T ], R d b), a forcing term f ∈ L 2 (Ω×[0, T ], R d f), and PDE coefficients c. The system of equations is:",
    "where N denotes a (potentially nonlinear) differential operator, and B encodes the boundary conditions.",
    "From an operator learning point of view, the objective is to approximate with a neural network G the temporal evolution operator G γ:",
    "For training, we assume access to a dataset of N solution trajectories, {u i } N i=1, where each trajectory is characterized by an initial condition u 0 i ∼ ν u 0 and environment-specific parameters γ i ∼ ν γ, and is observed over a spatial grid X i and on a temporal horizon [0, T ].",
    "Since the parameters γ i are unobserved, we supply the neural network with additional information beyond the current state u t i to help resolve this ambiguity."
